{
  "text": "Note that the algebra R g,0 (W ) is isomorphic to the subalgebra R g (W ) of the rational Cherednik algebra H g (W ) given as R g (W ) = \u03c1(R g,0 (W )). Furthermore, the central quotient R g,0 (W )/(H + 1) is a flat family of non-homogeneous quadratic Poincar\u00e9-Birkhoff-Witt algebras in the sense of [CITATION_1] . Indeed, let us consider the central quotient of the algebra H N,N +1 w, where w \u2208 W , i rs \u2208 N \u222a {0}, i N,N +1 \u2264 1, and monomials have no crossings. It is also clear that all the defining relations of the algebra R g,0 (W )/(H + 1) are quadratic.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17946074"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "17946074": {
      "title": "Poincar\u00e9-Birkhoff-Witt theorem for quadratic algebras of Koszul type",
      "abstract": "In this paper we discuss a generalization of the classica PBW-theorem to the case of Koszul algebras. Our result is a slight generalization of that obtained by A.Polischuk and L.Positselsky, but the proof is different and uses deformation theory."
    }
  }
}